{
  "text": "Microarray technology has accelerated our ability to understand the transcriptomes in various species and tissues. Using microarray, several studies have addressed to elucidate the effect of dietary n-3 PUFAs on mRNA expression in central nervous system (CNS) [CITATION_1] , liver [CITATION_2] and intestine [CITATION_3] . In the current study, we characterized gene expression signatures in the longissimus dorsi muscle of pigs fed with a linseed-enriched diet for 0, 30, 60 or 90 d using Affymetrix Genechip.",
